```@echo off

if "%~1" == "" goto error
if "%~2" == "" goto error
if "%~3" == "" goto error

set "target=%~1"
set "dest=%~2"
set "filename=%~3"

rem Replace the target symbol with the destination symbol in the file name
ren "%filename%" "%filename:%target%=%dest%"

rem Replace the target symbol with the destination symbol in the file contents
for /f "delims=" %%i in ('type "%filename%"') do (
  set "line=%%i"
  set "line=%line:%target%=%dest%"
  echo %line%
) > temp.txt
move /y temp.txt "%filename%"

goto end

:error
echo Error: Missing parameter

:end```
